## Review Checklist

### Nuxt Conventions

- [ ] `<script setup lang="ts">` used in all Vue files
- [ ] Auto-imports used (no manual import of `ref`, `computed`, etc.)
- [ ] `useFetch` or `$fetch` for API calls
- [ ] File-based routing for pages and server routes
- [ ] Composables in `composables/` directory
- [ ] Pinia stores use Composition API syntax

### Performance

- [ ] Lazy loading for heavy components (`<LazyComponent />`)
- [ ] Images use `<NuxtImg>` or `<NuxtPicture>`
- [ ] No unnecessary watchers or computed properties
- [ ] Server routes used for server-side logic

### Code Quality

- [ ] TypeScript strict mode (no `any`)
- [ ] Named exports for composables and utilities
- [ ] Props have proper TypeScript types
- [ ] Error states handled in templates

### Testing

- [ ] Tests exist for new composables and components
- [ ] Happy path and error cases tested

## Verdict Format

Return ONE of: **APPROVED**, **NEEDS_CHANGES**, or **BLOCKED**

```markdown
## Review: <VERDICT>

### Summary
<1-2 sentence summary>

### Issues (if any)
1. **[file:line]** <description>

### What Looks Good
- <positive feedback>
```
